<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width;">

    <style>

.btnn {
justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
    }
.myButton {
  background-color: #4CAF50; /* Green background */
  border: none; /* Remove default border */
  color: white; /* White text */
  padding: 15px 32px; /* Add padding (top/bottom, left/right) */
  text-align: center; /* Center the text */
  text-decoration: none; /* Remove underline for anchor tags */
  display: inline-block; /* Make the element a block for width/padding */
  font-size: 16px; /* Increase font size */
  margin: 4px 2px; /* Add some margin */
  cursor: pointer; /* Change cursor to a hand pointer */
  border-radius: 8px; /* Rounded corners */
}
@media print {
@page {
    size: 8.5in 11in;
    margin: 0; /* Optional: adjust margins as needed */
  }
  body {
    width: 8.5in;
    height: 11in;
  }
}
    #pdf-content {
        /* Ensure content doesn't break in the middle of text/images */
        page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
}
        /* CSS to style your content */
        #content-to-export {
            width: 8.5in; /* Set width to target size */
            padding: 20px;
            background: white;
height: 11in;
justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
        }


        /* Mobile styles (default) */
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            width: 95%;
            background: #f0f0f0;
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
 justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
        }
h1 {
font-size: 2rem;
 text-align: center;
}
.container img {
display: block;
  margin: auto;
  width: 40%;
}
 .container {
            background: white;
        width: 90%;
            border-radius: 8px;
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
 justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
        }


        /* Desktop styles (screens wider than 768px) */
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            body {
                background: #d1d1d1;
               /* display: inline-block;*/
                justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
width:95%;
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
            }
.container img {
display: block;
  margin: auto;
  width: 40%;
}
            .container {
                width: 90%; /* Mimics a fixed window feel */
padding-left: 5%;
padding-right: 5%;
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
 justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
            }
        }


.flex-container h2 {

box-shadow: 0 4px 10px blue;
border-radius: 8px;
width: 45%;
padding-top: 5%;
padding-left:3%;
padding-right: 2%;
font-size: 1.5rem;
margin-top: 2.5%;
margin-bottom: 2.5%;
}

.flex-container {
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px blue;
border-radius: 8px;
background: white;
paddint-left: 2%;
padding-right: 2%;
margin-top: 5%;
margin-bottom: 2.5%;
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap; /* Allows items to wrap to the next line */
 /* gap: 5%;  Optional: Adds space between the items */
/*  justify-content: space-between;  Optional: Distributes space evenly */
}

.flex-container img {
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px blue;
border-radius: 8px;
  /* Calculates width to be less than 50% to leave room for the gap */
  width: calc(48% - 5px);
  height: auto;
  /* Ensures padding and border are included in the width calculation */
  box-sizing: border-box;
  /* Ensures images maintain aspect ratio and fill space nicely */
  object-fit: cover;
margin-top: 2.5%;
margin-bottom: 2.5%;
margin-left:2%;
}
h4 {
position: absolute;
    top: 5%;
    right: 5%;
    margin: 10px; /* Optional: adds a small space from the edges */
}
    </style>
</head>



<body>
<h4>Company Logo<br>Company Address</h4>
 <div class="container">
        <h1><br>Field Report</h1>
<h2>We are please to present the following report</p>

<p>Address: <br> 2362 Wyecroft Road Unit 2<br>Oakville, Ontario<br>L6L 6M1</p>
<p><br>Contact:<br>Daniel Dosen<br>M: 905.288.7766<br>C: 416.833.9984<br>E:  daniel@everlastexteriors.ca<br>W: www.everlastexteriors.ca</p>
<p>Date Submited: March 3, 2026</p>
<p>This is just a quick template that I put together, something really basic. This would make reports available to the office within seconds after the upload as it can be accessed from the office or on the road. I would have to build a login page to ensure only people with the proper credentials are able to view the reports submitted.<br><br></p>
<p>The submit report button at the bottom of the page is disabled as this would be what would trigger the completion of the report.</p>
<p>You can play around with the template if you would like, photo and description is required or else the system rejects the upload.</p>
<p><br><br></p>
<hr>
<p><br><br></p>
<form action="/" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">

              <label for="image">Upload Image</label>
              <input type="file" id="image" name="image" accept="image/*" required />
                <label for="description"><br>Description: </label>
                <input type="text" id="description" name="description" cols="40" rows="5" required />

                <id="address" name="address" />

            <p></p>

<button class="btnn" type="submit" onclick="window.Android.showToast('Button clicked!')">Upload File</button>

            <p><br></p>
        </form>
</hr>
</div>

<div class="flex-container">

<% if (items.length > 0) { %>
            <% items.forEach(item => { %>

                    <img src="data:<%= item.img.contentType %>;base64,<%= item.img.data.toString('base64') %>"/>
<h2><%= item.img.description %><br><br></h2>

            <% }); %>
        <% } %>
</div>

<button class="myButton">Submit Report</button>

</body>
</html>
